4.2. Manual Testing Checklist

The following core features must be manually tested to ensure a good user experience and full CRUD functionality:

Card Creation (C):

Action: Enter valid Question/Answer and click "Add Flashcard".

Expected: Card appears at the top of the list; success toast is displayed.

Action: Try to submit with an empty Question or Answer.

Expected: Warning toast is displayed; card is NOT created.

Card Reading (R) & Real-time:

Action: Open the app and observe the list.

Expected: All previously created cards are visible in a responsive grid.

Card Flip Functionality:

Action: Click the card/flip button.

Expected: Card flips to show the Answer, then flips back to the Question.

Card Update (U):

Action: Click the Edit icon (blue pencil).

Expected: Text areas appear pre-filled.

Action: Change the Question and click Save (green checkmark).

Expected: Card reverts to display mode with new content; success toast is displayed.

Card Deletion (D):

Action: Click the Delete icon (red trashcan).

Expected: Confirmation box appears. Confirm deletion. The card disappears from the list; info toast is displayed.

Authentication & UI:

Action: Verify the header when the app loads.

Expected: The "User ID" is displayed, confirming a successful connection to Firebase/Firestore.